'''''California Technical Bulletin 117''''' ('''TB 117''') is a California [[law|fire safety law]], first implemented in 1975. It has recently been updated as a Technical Bulletin 117-2013. The law requires furniture to meet certain fire safety standards.<ref name=Standen> {{cite web | last = Standen | first = Amy | title = It’s Official: Toxic Flame Retardants No Longer Required in Furniture | work = | publisher =[[KQED|KQED Science]] | date =21 November 2013 | url = http://blogs.kqed.org/science/2013/11/21/its-official-toxic-flame-retardants-no-longer-required-in-furniture/ | accessdate =1 June 2014}}</ref><ref name=sofastorm> {{cite web |last=Standen |first=Amy |title=The Political Firestorm Inside Your Sofa |work= |publisher=KQED and QUEST Northern California ("a collaboration of six public broadcasters around the country") |date=6 April 2012 |url=http://science.kqed.org/quest/audio/the-political-firestorm-inside-your-sofa/ |accessdate=1 June 2014 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140113152016/http://science.kqed.org/quest/audio/the-political-firestorm-inside-your-sofa/ |archivedate=13 January 2014 |df= }}</ref><ref name=Watt> {{cite web | last = Watt | first = Brian | title = Fire-retardants in furniture: manufacturers adjust to CA′s new standards | work = | publisher = [[KPCC]] | date =26 December 2013 | url = http://www.scpr.org/blogs/economy/2013/12/26/15473/fire-retardants-in-furniture-manufacturers-adjust/ | accessdate =1 June 2014}}</ref><ref name=require> {{cite web | last = TB 117 | first = | title = Requirements, Test Procedure and Apparatus for Testing the Flame Retardance of Resilient Filling Materials Used in Upholstered Furniture | work = | publisher =[[State of California]] | date =March 2000 | url =http://www.bearhfti.ca.gov/industry/117.pdf | accessdate =1 June 2014}}</ref><ref> {{cite web | last = TB 117-2013 | first = | title = Requirements, Test Procedure and Apparatus for Testing the Flame Retardance of Resilien